Growing from base of Senna siamea (Fabaceae) in seasonally dry secondary coastal forest. A laccate Ganoderma with a deceptively dull surface. Appears to be perennial, with evidence a second tube layer. Widely adhered specimen with multiple pilei, second specimen stipitate, possibly growing from buried root.
